      • startSession

        public void startSession(AylaAuthProvider provider,
                         com.android.volley.Response.Listener<AylaAuthorization> successListener,
                         ErrorListener errorListener)
        Initializes and starts a new session for a user signing in to Ayla service using the authentication provider required for this app.

        This method logs the user in, and if successful creates a AylaDeviceManager, fetches the current AccountSettings from the server and notifies any AylaSessionManager.SessionManagerListener listeners that have registered that the session has been started.

        At this point the DeviceManager will fetch the list of devices from the server and begin polling them for updates.

        If the user wishes to log out, the application should call stopSession() to shut down the library and clean up.
        参数:
        provider - Auth provider for this app.
        successListener - Listener to receive the AylaAuthorization when sign-in is complete
        errorListener - Listener to receive an error should one occur

                                      AMAPCore.DeviceNotificationListener listener)
        Sets or clears notifications on all devices.
        参数:
        notificationType - Type of notification to set / clear
        enable - true to set the notification, false to clear it
        listener - listener to be notified when the job is done
